The paper focuses on the estimation of low-complexity signals observed through quantized compressive measurements, which is a topic that falls under the umbrella of compressed sensing (cs). The use of quantized measurements suggests that information theory (IT) may be relevant, as well as machine learning (LG) and signal processing (SP). The mention of low-rank matrices and compressible signals suggests that matrix methods (MM) and computer vision (CV) may also be relevant. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.IT, cs.LG, cs.SP, cs.MM, and cs.CV, in that order.
